{"body": "@al2o3cr  I didn't know `Hashie::Mash`, thanks for sharing it.\r\n\r\nAlthough `Hashie::Mash.new` or `include Hashie::Extensions::MethodAccess` should behave similar to my proposal, we need to add a new gem dependency. My proposal is only when using `delegate` to a Hash treat keys/values as attribute accessors.\r\n\r\n@pftg `serialize` was just an example, the focus is on the `delegate`.  \r\n\r\nBTW, it is only a proposal. Even being nice in my example, it may not be interesting to add it into `delegate`.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/20523136", "created_at": "2013-07-05T14:59:17Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/11262#issuecomment-20523136", "updated_at": "2013-07-08T02:27:07Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 11262, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/phstc", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/1e9ce2c15d24684d45ae475c5d9fc4d4?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff2edaa0602de5995ee08d2e9124b1e9d.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/received_events", "gravatar_id": "1e9ce2c15d24684d45ae475c5d9fc4d4", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "phstc", "type": "User", "id": 105652, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/phstc/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237d6ebbd3543c151008326"}, "id": 20523136, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/11262"}
